A man has gone on hunger strike to protest at the deportation of lawyer Miguna Miguna. For the third day, Boniface Akumu kept vigil at Kondele roundabout to demand that the Government bring back the opposition figure. ALSO READ:

Miguna leaves Dubai for Canada Rugged and dirty, Akumu has been lying on the ground resting his head on a bag which has a change of clothes which he wears to keep warm when the weather changes. When The Standard visited him yesterday, a small crowd of youths stood watching from a distance while passersby stopped briefly to read his protest message on a banner. Reports indicated that the lawyer had arrived in Canada from Dubai. Akumu has vowed to continue with his hunger strike until the Government obeys High Court orders to facilitate Miguna's return. Avoid fake news! Subscribe to the Standard SMS service and receive factual, verified breaking news as it happens. Text the word 'NEWS' to 22840 He said he last ate on Thursday last week. He claimed his family supported his protest. “I do not care even if I die of hunger. I have been very unhappy with the way the State has been abusing the rule of law,” said Akumu. ALSO READ:

